  "body": "### Add tokens sold to Crowdsale contract\r\n\r\nIt would be nice if we could have a variable `uint256 public tokensSold` so as to keep track of the amount of tokens that have been sold so far during a TGE event. \r\n\r\nThen, the `buyTokens()` function should look like:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  function buyTokens(address beneficiary) public payable {\r\n    require(beneficiary != 0x0);\r\n    require(validPurchase());\r\n\r\n    uint256 weiAmount = msg.value;\r\n\r\n    // calculate token amount to be created\r\n    uint256 tokens = weiAmount.mul(rate);\r\n\r\n    // update state\r\n    weiRaised = weiRaised.add(weiAmount);\r\n    tokensSold = tokensSold.add(tokens); --> new line\r\n\r\n    token.mint(beneficiary, tokens);\r\n    TokenPurchase(msg.sender, beneficiary, weiAmount, tokens);\r\n\r\n    forwardFunds();\r\n  }\r\n```\r\nThis will have the same philosophy as the `weiRaised` variable... We want to keep track of the wei raised to do checks, to have different crowdsale implementations like `CappedCrowdsale.sol` and  `RefundableCrowdsale.sol`, among others. \r\n\r\nHaving the `tokensSold` variable will let us, for instance, have a `CappedOnTokensCrowdsale.sol` or a `RefundableOnTokensCrowdsale.sol` where the `cap` and `goal` (respectively) are expressed in amount of tokens rather than in amount of wei.\r\n",
